--- Vercel Migration Checklist ---

1. Sign up at https://vercel.com/ and connect your GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket account.
2. Import your repository into Vercel.
3. Set your project root to the folder containing your static site (e.g., /website).
4. Ensure your serverless functions are in an `api/` directory at the project root (Vercel uses /api for functions).
5. Install any backend dependencies (e.g., `resend`) in your project root (`npm install resend`).
6. Set environment variables (e.g., RESEND_API_KEY) in the Vercel dashboard under Project Settings > Environment Variables.
7. Update your frontend to call `/api/send-estimate-email` instead of Netlify's `/.netlify/functions/send-estimate-email`.
8. Deploy and test your site and functions.
9. (Optional) Set up a custom domain in Vercel.

--- End Checklist ---

--- How to Set Up Vercel ---

1. Go to [https://vercel.com/](https://vercel.com/) and sign up (use your GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket account).
2. Click "Add New Project" and import your repository.
3. When prompted, set the **project root** to your static site folder (e.g., `/website`).
4. Ensure your serverless functions are in `/api` at the project root (e.g., `/website/api/send-estimate-email.js`).
5. In your project root, run `npm install resend` to install backend dependencies.
6. In the Vercel dashboard, go to your project > Settings > Environment Variables and add any needed variables (e.g., `RESEND_API_KEY`).
7. Update your frontend code to call `/api/send-estimate-email` for your email API.
8. Click "Deploy" in Vercel. Your site will be live on a vercel.app domain.
9. (Optional) Set up a custom domain in Vercel > Settings > Domains.

--- End Vercel Setup Guide ---